    'Plate twist',
    '{"merged_steps": ["Step 1: Sit on an exercise mat with your legs extended in front of you.", "Step 2: Grasp a plate in both hands as if holding a steering wheel, arms slightly bent, and hold it in front of your abdominals.", "Step 3: With knees slightly bent, cross your ankles and slowly lift them a few inches off the floor.", "Step 4: Keep your back straight but lean backward slightly to help maintain balance.", "Step 5: Exhaling, rotate your torso (twist) to the right side and touch the end of the plate to the floor.", "Step 6: Inhale and return to the forward facing start position.", "Step 7: Exhaling, rotate your torso (twist) to the left side and touch the end of the plate to the floor.", "Step 8: Inhale and return to the forward facing start position.", "Step 9: Repeat for a full set."], "sources": [{"source": "wger", "file": "C:\\Users\\kaiqu\\Desktop\\SOMMA\\datasets\\wger-master\\wger\\exercises\\fixtures\\exercise-base-data.json", "steps": ["Step 1: Sit on an exercise mat with your legs extended in front of you.", "Step 2: Grasp a plate in both hands as if holding a steering wheel, arms slightly bent, and hold it in front of your abdominals.", "Step 3: With knees slightly bent, cross your ankles and slowly lift them a few inches off the floor.", "Step 4: Keep your back straight but lean backward slightly to help maintain balance.", "Step 5: Exhaling, rotate your torso (twist) to the right side and touch the end of the plate to the floor.", "Step 6: Inhale and return to the forward facing start position.", "Step 7: Exhaling, rotate your torso (twist) to the left side and touch the end of the plate to the floor.", "Step 8: Inhale and return to the forward facing start position.", "Step 9: Repeat for a full set."], "description": "Step 1: Sit on an exercise mat with your legs extended in front of you. Step 2: Grasp a plate in both hands as if holding a steering wheel, arms slightly bent, and hold it in front of your abdominals. Step 3: With knees slightly bent, cross your ankles and slowly lift them a few inches off the floor. Step 4: Keep your back straight but lean backward slightly to help maintain balance. Step 5: Exhaling, rotate your torso (twist) to the right side and touch the end of the plate to the floor. Step 6: Inhale and return to the forward facing start position. Step 7: Exhaling, rotate your torso (twist) to the left side and touch the end of the plate to the floor. Step 8: Inhale and return to the forward facing start position. Step 9: Repeat for a full set."}], "summary": "Step 1: Sit on an exercise mat with your legs extended in front of you. Step 2: Grasp a plate in both hands as if holding a steering wheel, arms slightly bent, and hold it in front of your abdominals. Step 3: With knees slightly bent, cross your ankles and slowly lift them a few inches off the floor. Step 4: Keep your back straight but lean backward slightly to help maintain balance. Step 5: Exhaling, rotate your torso (twist) to the right side and touch the end of the plate to the floor. Step 6: Inhale and return to the forward facing start position. Step 7: Exhaling, rotate your torso (twist) to the left side and touch the end of the plate to the floor. Step 8: Inhale and return to the forward facing start position. Step 9: Repeat for a full set.", "setup": "Step 1: Sit on an exercise mat with your legs extended in front of you.", "eccentric": "Step 2: Grasp a plate in both hands as if holding a steering wheel, arms slightly bent, and hold it in front of your abdominals.", "concentric": "Step 3: With knees slightly bent, cross your ankles and slowly lift them a few inches off the floor.", "safety": "Step 9: Repeat for a full set."}'::jsonb,
